This paper deals with natural language processing and neural networks, which are typically covered in the arXiv sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Given the focus on language and neural networks, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. However, the paper also discusses the presence of local minima and the need for stronger inductive biases, which are more commonly discussed in cs.NE and cs.CV.
